<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-217-380 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 376 893</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Feb 25 1991 v8 n8 p37(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>STSC recasts stat package's Experiment Design. (Statgraphicsstatistical software) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ferranti, Marc.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   STSC Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Statgraphics 5.0 (Statistical software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionStatistical Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Marc FerrantiandM;Revamped experiment-design features are among the highlights of STSC Inc.'snew version of its Statgraphics statistical software, which also includesimproved documentation and enhancements to statistical procedures.andM;Like earlier versions, Statgraphics 5.0, slated to be shipped in mid-March,allows users to edit statistics data by manipulating graphs, and vice versa,according to Ed Beemer, a spokesman for the Rockville, Md., company.andM;In addition, version 5.0 incorporates a host of new graph types in theExperimental Design section of the program, he said.andP;  The new graphs includePareto charts, interaction plots, main effects plots, square plots and cubeplots.andM;Statgraphics' Experimental Design section has been enhanced with a widervariety of screening-design procedures, as well as response-surface-designprocedures, which previously had been included in other sections of thesoftware.andM;The screening-design procedures are used in the initial stages of anexperiment to help determine which criteria are most important, according toSTSC Statistical Consultant Sarita Fernandes.andP;  The response-surfaceprocedures are then used for in-depth analysis and to narrow the necessarycriteria.andM;New capabilities in the experiment-design section include enhancedmultivariate Analysis of Variance (ANOVA) procedures that support unbalanceddesigns, repeated-measures designs and partially nested designs.andM;Beta testers said the enhanced Experimental Design section was particularlyuseful to novice statisticians.andM;&quot;The experiment-design catalog has increased, giving you more flexibility insetting up your experiment,&quot; said Richard Clark, a group quality assuranceengineer for James River Corp., a paper manufacturer in Bedford Park, Ill.andO;&quot;It's menu-driven, and the experiment-design menus now also includeresponse-surface procedures, which make it easier to navigate the softwareand set up experiments.&quot;andM;STSC officials stressed the importance of the updated documentation, whichnow includes the Statistical Procedures Reference Manual, with a chapter foreach Statgraphics procedure.andP;  Since Statgraphics is aimed at novicestatisticians as well as professionals, such comprehensive documentation is anecessity, Beemer said.andM;Statgraphics 5.0, which requires 640K bytes of RAM and a hard disk, costs$995.andM;STSC Inc. can be reached at (301) 984-5000.andO;</TEXT></DOC>